               <head>Ghazzali's Kimiya us-sa'adah</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Kīmiyā-yi saʿādat by Abū Ḥāmid Muḥammad ibn Muḥammad ibn Aḥmad al-Ghazzālī, 1058-1111</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85089353 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807 " n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_66x-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100000000565.0x000205 viaf_31996761">Abū Ḥāmid Muḥammad ibn Muḥammad ibn Aḥmad al-Ghazzālī, 1058-1111</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100000000565.0x000205 viaf_31996761">ابو حامد محمد غزالى طوسى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_20476">Kīmiyā-yi saʿādat</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_20476">كيمياى سعادت</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Famous treatise on Sufism according to Sunnī doctrine by the Yaminid theologian, al-Ghazzālī
al-Ṭūsī</p>
                        <p>Defective at beginning
</p>
                        <p>Not dated, but reproduces the colophon of the original source, dated (f. 51v): Wednesday, 5 Rabīʿ al-Avval 1099/9 January 1688 or regnal year 32 of Emperor <persName key="viaf_6178410" role="oth">ʿĀlamgīr I</persName>
                        </p>
                        <p>Annotations of later owner’s: 1) <persName key="person_f7277" role="fmo  ann">Mawlavī Muḥammad Aʿẓam Kashmīrī</persName> in dār al-khilāfah <placeName>Shāhjahānābād</placeName>; 2) <persName key="person_f7227" role="fmo ann">Khvājah ʿĪd/ʿAnbar</persName>
                        </p>
                        <p>Included at end (f. 52v), two recipes for medicated qahvah
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian </textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
